## Interview Question 2: Difference between JDK, JRE, and JVM

| Feature        | JVM                     | JRE                                       | JDK                                   |
| -------------- | ----------------------- | ----------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- |
| Full Form      | Java Virtual Machine    | Java Runtime Environment                  | Java Development Kit                  |
| Purpose        | Runs Java bytecode      | Provides environment to run Java programs | Used to develop and run Java programs |
| Contains       | Executes `.class` files | JVM + Libraries                           | JRE + Development tools               |
| Tools Included | No                      | No compiler                               | Includes `javac`, debugger, jar tools |
| Used By        | End users/system        | End users                                 | Developers                            |

### Relationship

```text
JDK = JRE + Development Tools
JRE = JVM + Libraries
```

### Easy Analogy

* JVM → Engine
* JRE → Car ready to drive
* JDK → Car factory with tools to build cars

